Based on the distributions of the dataset, some observations that can be made are:

  1. Cost of the Order:
  • The Dristribution of the Order Cost appears to be skewed to the right, insinuating that most orders have a lower cost.
  • There are a few orders with higher costs, resulting in the long tail on the right of the distribution curve
  1. Rating:
  • The Rating Distribution indicates that the median of the rating is 4, with some fluctuation within the upper quartile.
  • There are no observable outliars, and the majority of raitings fall within the 3-5 scaale.
  1. Day of the Week:
  • As observed, there is a slightly higher number of orders on the Weekdays compared to the Weekends.
  1. Food Preparation Time:
  • This distribution is right-skewed, showing that the majority of orders have shoer preparation time.
  • There are a few orders with longer preparation times, creating a long tail towards the right of the distribution.
  1. Delivery Time:
  • The Delivery time peaks around the center of the distribution, indicating that most orders arrive their destination within the 25 to 30 minute mark
  • Furthermore, the distribution reveals that a larger number of orders take less than the above mentioned time-frame compared to the orders that take longer to be deliverd

Question 14: The company charges the restaurant 25% on the orders having cost greater than 20 dollars and 15% on the orders having cost greater than 5 dollars. Find the net revenue generated by the company across all orders. [3 marks]

In [71]:
# Calculate the commission for each order
df["commission"] = 0
df.loc[df["cost_of_the_order"] > 20, "commission"] = df["cost_of_the_order"] * 0.25
df.loc[(df["cost_of_the_order"] > 5) & (df["cost_of_the_order"] <= 20), "commission"] = df["cost_of_the_order"] * 0.15

# Calculate the net revenue
net_revenue = df["cost_of_the_order"].sum() - df["commission"].sum()

# Print the result
print(f"Net revenue generated by the company is ${net_revenue}")

Net revenue generated by the company is $25148.517

Question 17: What are your conclusions from the analysis? What recommendations would you like to share to help improve the business? (You can use cuisine type and feedback ratings to drive your business recommendations.) [6 marks]

CONCLUSIONS:

  1. Cost of the Order:
  • The maority of the orders have a relatively low cost, with only a low percentage of orders with a higher cost.
  1. Rating:
  • Ratings are generally positive with the greater majority falling within the 3-5 range
  1. Day of the Week:
  • There is a slightly higher count of orders on Weekdays compared to Weekends
  1. Food Preparation Time:
  • Most Common orders have shorter food preparation time, only a few outliars have a high frequency that corrosponds with the longer preparation time.
  1. Delivery Time:
  • The Delivery time peaks around the center of the distribution, indicating that most orders arrive their destination within the 25 to 30 minute mark
  • Furthermore, the distribution reveals that a larger number of orders take less than the above mentioned time-frame compared to the orders that take longer to be deliverd

RECOMMENDATIONS:

  1. Promotional Offer Criteria::
  • Following the Promotional offers mentioned above, find ways to encourage customers to leave more reviews using incentives such as order points.
  1. Analysis of Cuisine Type
  • Consider promoting or featuring cuisines with higher rating.
  1. Customer Engagement:
  • Impliment programs such as a reward-point system, cupons and exclusive membership discounts. This can also be used to encourage customer ratings.
  1. Time Management:
  • Employ technological strategies to streamline and reduce the preparation and delivery time.
  1. Marketing and Pricing:
  • Highlight special promotions, events and discounts to increase orders over the Weekends.
  • Review the pricing strategy for the higher cost products and consider reviewing the cost of some popular cuisines.
